          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":40,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"sunday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"14 km at easy pace (5:52-6:43/km). Keep effort conversational throughout. This establishes your long-run baseline heading into the plan.\"},\"monday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest. You ran long yesterday. Let the adaptation begin.\"},\"tuesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"8 km easy (5:52-6:43/km). Legs should feel loose by the second half. If they do not, slow down.\"},\"wednesday\":{\"slot_type\":\"CrossTrain\",\"workout_type\":\"CrossTrain\",\"notes\":\"30-40 min low-impact cross-training. Cycling or swimming preferred. Keeps aerobic stimulus without adding run stress.\"},\"thursday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"notes\":\"8 km total. Include 20 min at threshold pace (4:53/km) with 10 min easy warm-up and 10 min easy cool-down. First quality session of the plan.\"},\"friday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest. Back-to-back quality and rest days are intentional. Recovery is part of the training load.\"},\"saturday\":{\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"10 km easy (5:52-6:43/km). Relaxed effort. Focus on running tall and keeping cadence smooth.\"},\"week_summary\":\"Week 1 of the Base phase. Total target is 40 km across 4 run days, matching your recent training volume. No jump in load this week. The goal is to establish the pattern: long run Sunday, one tempo mid-week, two easy support runs. The Daniels-Gilbert zones set your paces from your 48:00 10K. Trust the easy pace range even when it feels slow. Aerobic base at this stage is built through volume at low intensity, not by pushing the moderate runs harder.\"}"
        }
      ]
    }
